    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSIXEL output written from Lua to stdout in Neovim TUI no longer appears on 0.12.0 in my environment, while the same payload appears correctly on 0.11.6 and 0.11.7.\nI verified that:\n- the PNG file exists,\n- chafa successfully generates SIXEL output (code=0, non-empty stdout),\n- rendering works outside Neovim in the same terminal session,\n- rendering via the same Lua command works in Neovim 0.11.x but not in 0.12.0.\nThis breaks terminal-image workflows (e.g. Typst preview plugins) that rely on escape-sequence rendering from Lua.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open Windows Terminal (PowerShell), and confirm chafa is installed: `chafa --version`\n2. Use any existing PNG file. Example: `C:/Users/Renato/AppData/Local/Temp/nvim/typst_preview/test.png`\n3. Verify it renders outside Neovim: `chafa -f sixel \"C:\\Users\\Renato\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\nvim\\typst_preview\\test.png\"`\n4. Start Neovim with no config: `nvim --clean`\n5. In Neovim command-line, run: `:lua local p='C:/Users/Renato/AppData/Local/Temp/nvim/typst_preview/test.png'; local r=vim.system({'chafa','-f','sixels','--size','68x48',p}):wait(); print('code',r.code,'out',#(r.stdout or '')); io.stdout:write('\\27[s\\27[2;142H'..(r.stdout or '')..'\\27[u')`\n6. Observe behavior by version:   - 0.11.6 / 0.11.7: image appears.\n   - 0.12.0: no image is displayed.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf SIXEL payload is successfully generated and written via Lua (io.stdout:write) in TUI, image should render as in 0.11.x.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1774638290 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo equivalent repro in Vim (vim -u DEFAULTS) because this case depends on Neovim Lua API + TUI behavior.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal (PowerShell profile)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom releases and Scoop (Windows package manager)",
